<p><placeName>State of Louisiana</placeName></p>

<p><placeName>Parish of Natchitoches</placeName> <date when="1824-00-09">Novm 9th 1824</date></p>

<p><persName>Col. Austin</persName></p>

<p>Sir After my respects to you I have to inform you, I am happy
to inform you that I am well, but I have had some sickness and 
misfortune in my <persName>family</persName>, I made all preperations for moving as soon
as I got home, but my <persName>wife </persName>was taken sick and remained in a very
low state a Long time and has not got over it yet, her sickness has
prevented my being able to move her this <date n="Winter-1824">winter </date>I have sent out
my stock and two of my <persName>sons </persName>in order to make a Crop, I will be on
my self as soon as the cituation of my <persName>wife </persName>and the Season will admit
of, <persName>Mr Lynch </persName>informs me that there is three Dollars and fifty Cents
required to be paid down in Cash for Sta[m]ped paper, on 
receiving the title, I have sent on the money for my own Deed and his, you
will if you think propper let my <persName>son </persName>or <persName>Mr Lynch</persName> have my deed, I
sepose you have made out my deed</p>

<p>[Endorsed:]  <persName>Martin Allin</persName> <placeName>Louisiana </placeName><date when="1824-11-09">9th Nov 1824</date></p>

        </div1>
